##On Earth the first day of the siege of Wuhan

Micro-signal Zairenjian11

Features, with a calm narrative against the cold | phoenix network produced in the human studio

At 2 a.m. on January 23,2020, Wuhan announced that it would close the city to traffic from 10 a.m. , and although many people were still sleeping, many left the city overnight within an eight-hour window. Many more have stayed, some have no choice, and some fear they are potential transmitters wherever they go. A director, a delivery man, and a unit staff, the first day of closure, what did they do, what kind of inner twists and turns? How do they live in an uncertain future?

This is the story of three people who stayed behind in Wuhan.

Accept the city as it is

Photo and caption by Wang Qiming

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
â– 7:00 a.m. , my roof, my dad's grape trellis.

I'm Wang Qiming, an independent film director. I live in downtown Wuhan. Today is January 23,2020, New Year twenty-nine, 4:00 am, I suddenly woke up without warning, due to these days of mental stress, the body has a very heavy sense of powerlessness. I really want to tell myself to go back to sleep and stop looking at my phone. Head down for a while, is no sleep, so picked up the phone, open the phone for a moment, heart buried for several days bomb finally exploded, Wuhan City closed!

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
â–  Masks from the House for the last two days.

In fact, these days also thought about whether the city will be closed, but did not think it would be this way without warning, in the early morning quietly released news. The hour between four and five, I was really desperate, the last line of Defense in my heart was completely broken, my body began to sink, my breathing became rapid, and I began to perspire constantly. I decided to get up, so I woke up my lover ML, who was still asleep, and told her that Wuhan was closed, and she said, bleary-eyed, is this your dream I smiled bitterly and said, look at your phone

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
â–  The supply of rubbing alcohol from the House for the last two days.

Ml and I discussed our plans briefly on the second floor and decided to head to the supermarket early to stock up on supplies and disinfectant. There was this overwhelming sense of urgency, and it was all negative, and it felt like the city had been abandoned, and it reminded me of Chernobyl and all the other disaster movies.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The neighborhood where I live.

The day slowly began to light up. The weather in Wuhan today was very bad. The morning fog was very heavy and the visibility was quite low. The whole city was still sleeping. I stood on the balcony and looked at the windows of my neighborhood, wondering if they'd wake up as desperate as I was.

Around 6:30, my parents woke up, and I went downstairs to tell them the truth, and my father was very calm, "It's a good thing, " he said. "Don't panic, don't panic, stay alert, take precautions. It's going to be a long battle. We just need to be prepared. " After talking to him, I felt a lot calmer and began to accept the fact. A sense of security, both familiar and unfamiliar, suddenly welled up in me, warm and powerful.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
â–  At 8 a.m. , we drive to the supermarket, wearing gloves the entire time we're in the car.

I work in Beijing on weekdays. On January 20th, my family and I discussed whether we should drive back to Beijing together. Both my parents and in-laws decided to stay in Wuhan (maybe they didn't feel the gravity of the situation at the time) , and my partner and I decided to stay in Wuhan with our parents. At the same time, we don't want to put pressure on other cities because we are also worried that we are potential disseminators. The family has been keeping a close eye on their physical changes these days.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
â–  A stray cat in front of the grocery store.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
â–  The streets of Wuhan in the morning.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
â–  At 8:00 in the morning, the moment YW opens its doors.

After 8 o'clock, ML and I drove to the YW supermarket. There were a lot of people waiting for the door to open. We could feel that everyone was a little unstable. Some began to ask the security staff to open the door quickly, something about how dangerous it is to have so many people at the door.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
â– 8:30 a.m. , YW supermarket workers.

After the supermarket opened, we still more orderly way to go in, not I imagine the scene of a swarm to rush into the scene.

Our shopping this time, mainly focus on the daily necessities, such as food and water, and cleaning disinfectant, half an hour, we filled two large shopping carts full.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
â– 9:00 a.m. , YW supermarket workers.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
â–  At 9:11 a.m. , workers inside the YW supermarket.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
â–  At 9:00 a.m. , hand sanitizer is dispensed at every entrance and exit of the supermarket.

More and more people are flocking to the supermarket as they exit. Thankfully, there is a special disinfection area at the entrance, and security guards prevent people from entering without masks.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
â–  The supermarket cashier also wears a mask.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
â–  At 9:00 a.m. , the parking lot of YX supermarket.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
â–  At 9:08 a.m. in front of the supermarket, nervous people waiting for taxis.

On the way back I saw a lot of people with suitcases and cabs. I respect their instinct and wish them good luck.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
â–  Cars are scarce on the way home from the supermarket.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
â–  Long lines formed at gas stations on the way back, most of them preparing to leave Wuhan to refuel.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
â–  The staff at the gas station.

Passing a gas station, I wanted to get more gas. As a result, there was a long queue at the gas station. Through the glass, I could see that many cars in front had trunks full of luggage. At the moment, I was really angry, i wanted to get out of the car and ask the owners what they thought, but ML stopped me.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
â–  The girl cried with her luggage and begged the driver to take her to the train station. The driver told her that the train had stopped running. The girl did not give up and continued to stop the train.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
People selling seafood and meat on the streets near the complex.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
â–  The neighborhood roadside, suddenly a lot of people selling all kinds of strange things.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
At 3:20 pm, when we got home, we began a thorough disinfection, using 84 disinfectant and WLS disinfectant to clean the house thoroughly. We then worked out procedures with our parents, such as putting on gloves, hats and glasses in addition to a mask in case we had to leave the house, disinfecting ourselves with alcohol before entering the House, and taking off our coats before entering the house.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
In the evening my mother cooked a delicious dinner, and the family discussed the present situation and how the future should be carried out in a calm and objective manner. I did not give too much opinion, but listened to their conversation in silence, finished a bowl of steaming pork ribs lotus root soup.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
After dinner, it began to rain outside, and I opened the window, hoping that the energy of love and compassion in our family would be released.

This is my experience of the first day of the siege of Wuhan, not so bad and not so optimistic, this account is also the real experience without any embellishment, finally quoted from the "Chernobyl" inside the line to end it:

We're so focused on finding the truth, that it doesn't occur to us that very few people want us to find something, but the truth is always there, whether we see it or choose to see it, the truth doesn't matter what we want or want.

Still got ta live. It's a lot of pressure

Photo / Yamaki

I'm a take-out rider. After the announcement, many of the delivery riders I know left Wuhan before 10 am. By now, I personally think more than 90% of the takeaway riders in Wuhan have left. Leaving or staying, I didn't hesitate much, not only because I had planned ahead of the outbreak, but also because I didn't want to be a potential source of infection and be irresponsible to my family back home.

â–  My rental house in Wuhan costs more than 600 yuan a month.

Born in 1990, I have two children, one in his mid 20s and one just a few months old, both living with my wife in her hometown in Nanyang, Henan Province. My Dad didn't know there was an epidemic in Wuhan until today, when he went to the street to get a haircut. Then he called me and told me not to go out. My wife also told me not to go to a crowded place, try to stay at home, do not pick up the single platform.

â–  When I return at night, the streets in my neighborhood are empty.

But now I don't know when the siege will end. A month? Seven, eight weeks? No single is no income, I rent a house in Wuhan, monthly rent more than 600..

â–  The streets are empty, and the cleaners are still standing.

Today, buses, subways, planes and ferries all stopped in Wuhan. I was riding my electric bike around the city. The street was deserted except for the dustmen who were still at their posts. There are only a few convenience stores, pharmacies, fast food restaurants... Open. Before the university holiday, I usually have 50 orders. But today only sent 4 orders, one is because the platform order is less, and the other is because I take orders short time today.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
â–  The delivery person is still delivering the order, and it may be quite a lot of people who are not able to travel, but they still need to place the order online for the delivery person to deliver the order. Several takeout did not stop, but orders are relatively small.

This 4 in send fruit to the villa area, the property only to the community door, said not to let take-away food into. Now the neighborhood doesn't want strangers in, potential sources of infection. Another job, I run errands to buy cigarettes and disinfection water, disinfection water out of stock, ran several to buy. There is also a young Internet cafe Internet, ordered a hamburger..

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
There will be some queues for supplies and medicine. The ordinary medical mask still has to sell, disinfects the water to be quite short some.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
â–  there weren't many people at the supermarket either, and they probably all bought yesterday and the day before yesterday.

In addition to delivering food, I rode my bike to see the city, the city, the supermarket, the train station, the vegetable market... I wanted to see if the situation was as bad as the internet said. When I walk through the city, it really has the feeling of the movie "Busan Line" , the city is very desolate, many supermarkets, shopping malls are closed, universities are closed. Some supermarket prices are very high, but HM fresh vegetable prices did not rise, feel that supplies can be, in addition to disinfection water, supplies are guaranteed.

â–  Now some properties and residential areas are forbidden to take-out and non-residents of this residential area into the, today encountered a few are the same. Residential property at the entrance to the door prepared disinfection water and so on, you can use it.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
â–  Here's my dinner for today.

This morning, as usual, I went to the usual home in Lanzhou to eat a bowl of noodles, but the boss said that tomorrow will be closed, to minimize contact with others. I talked to my boss earlier, and he said the whole Spring Festival was open. I think there is a lot of pressure on the people of the city, right, if there is no city, the store must still open. I got up late in the morning. After eating this bowl of noodles, I drank some water at noon and bought instant noodles and sausages at the convenience store in the evening.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
â–  This is the only kitchen utensil in my rental house.

What worries me is how I eat next, I rarely cook by myself -- I'm at my busiest time in Florida. With fewer menus and fewer places to eat, the only thing I have in my house is an electric cooker, and I'm wondering if I should buy an induction cooker and Cook my own food.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Today, I wore a company subsidized surgical mask throughout the day, and riders could pick up an antiviral oral solution at any pharmacy. Today although receives the order to be few, but the company still subsidized more than 100 yuan, the platform still encouraged us to stick to one's post. I'll go out again tomorrow, probably with a list of convenience stores, drugstores, and fruit stores.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

Looking at the stop sign, I fell down

Text / Picture / concave eye

I am a native of Wuhan and live in Hankou. Wake up at seven o'clock in the morning, see the mobile phone on the news of the city of Wuhan closed, the heart is calm. As early as December 31 last year, I saw the news of The Paper's report, "the expert team from the National Health Commission has arrived in Wuhan with pneumonia of unknown cause found in Wuhan. " Then began to Wuhan this pneumonia epidemic warning... so far, I only hope that the government will make every effort to minimize the possible harm caused by this epidemic.

At 8:00 in the morning, the family needs to buy enough green vegetables for the Spring Festival. Dad Worried about the epidemic, do not trust me to go out shopping, I argued with him, twist, had to comply with his wishes, told him to be careful.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
9:00, Dad comes home from the grocery store, and I can't wait to ask him what's going on out there. The neighborhood was quiet and empty, he said. No sign of the old men or women who exercise. Supermarket stream of people, are to buy vegetables and spices, the basic are wearing a mask. The supermarket cashier, who may not be wearing a mask because of a question-and-answer problem, stepped forward to gently remind him of the dangers of not wearing a mask.

Dad said the neighborhood next to the market closed tomorrow, food is still rich, but prices are 50% higher than usual, and some even doubled, a large bag of vegetables spent more than 400 yuan. He stopped by a nearby pharmacy, where supplies of face masks, alcohol, thermometers, and so-called targeted Chinese patent medicines and Western medicines were out of stock.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
At 10:00, all kinds of public transport in Wuhan were suspended. I was still shocked to see my wechat friends sending me the picture of the subway gate slowly falling during the day. Feel that the government in the spread of the epidemic prevention efforts are very strong, but in the guarantee of safe living in the epidemic area, the measures, it is difficult to call convenient.

Then I started scanning through information about the epidemic, relaying important facts published by authoritative media, and fighting false claims of all kinds.

And so on until 3:00 in the afternoon, I felt sleepy, so I took a nap. When I woke up, I had the courage to go out and see what was going on in the world: it was dark and drizzly, there was a long line of cars waiting outside the gas station, most restaurants were closed, only a few were still open; There is indeed a shortage of green vegetables in the supermarket, and the vendor standing in front of the market laments that people lock themselves in their homes and that business is no longer viable. The otherwise busy traffic lanes are sparsely populated, with only the "year of the rat 2020" character on the electronic bulletin board adding a warm glow to the empty streets..

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Finally, when I saw a stop sign for pneumonia at the entrance of the subway station, I lost my footing and fell on a shared bicycle, pulling my padded jacket out with a big slit, i can only helplessly see those fine threads shivering in the cold wind. In an instant, I just want to hurry home, take a hot bath, calm my heart surging panic.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Life goes on, and the people around you need to be protected, and real change will only begin to happen if individuals once again summon the courage to face it all.
